process help=*
parm pipename    type=(string,99)
local dumstring string
parm strvar  type=name default="dumstring"
end-proc
.title
VICAR Program fifor - reads value from named pipe
.help
PURPOSE

     FIFOR reads the value parameter from the named pipe

.PAGE
TAE COMMAND LINE FORMAT

     local somestrvar string
     fifor pipename=thePipeName strvar=somestrvar

.PAGE
OPERATION

     FIFOR reads the value parameter from the named pipe and copies it
     to strvar.

.PAGE
     
RESTRICTIONS

     The named pipe must exist and be readable. This program will block
     until there is a value to read.

.PAGE
WRITTEN BY:            W. L. Bunch, Wed Feb 21 2007

COGNIZANT PROGRAMMER:  W. L. Bunch

REVISIONS: 
  Wed Feb 21 2007    Initial version
  Sat Dec 29 2007 wlb switched to USES_ANSI_C AND LIB_CARTO; misc cleanup

.level1
.var pipename
The pipe name (created with system command "mkfifo").
.var strvar
TAE string variable to read into.
.end
